  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2022-03-17",
    "date": "2022-04-22T19:10:03Z",
    "text": "Hotels for Heroes Act of 2022\n\nThis bill requires public lodging establishments to waive any minimum age requirements to obtain accommodation for members of the Armed Forces who present a valid identification card and seek to obtain accommodation while under military orders or on authorized military leave. A knowing violation of this requirement is punishable by fine."
  },
